In a viral video, a police officer is seen demanding bribe from
some persons in police station Ramban. Police in its version termed that the said video is of year 2020 and made viral again with malicious intentions to malign the image of district police Ramban.

The said video was recorded months back by a person namely Dilbagh Singh S/O Ranjeet Singh relative of Ranjeet Singh who was involved in Case FIR NO 174/2020 U/S 462,323,504,506.

The said person wanted to lodge a counter FIR on false allegations and fake evidences against the complainants of above said case.

The district chief of the Ramban took cognisance of the incident once the alleged video surfaced on the social media and the said officer was put under suspension and a departmental enquiry was initiated against the delinquent officer.

**District Jammu Thang-Ta Championship 2024-25 Concludes Successfully**

*Baba Kelakh Nath Hall, Bantlab, Jammu, August 18, 2024* – The District Jammu Thang-Ta Championship 2024-25, held at Baba Kelakh Nath Hall, Bantlab, concluded today with great enthusiasm and spirit. The two-day event, organized by District Jammu Thang-Ta Association in collaboration with J&K Thang-Ta Association sponsered by J&K sports council from August 17th to 18th, witnessed participation from more than 220 students from various schools and clubs across the district, showcasing their exceptional skills and sportsmanship.Chetan Academy Bajalta is Overall Champion in this Tournament and New Brook dail Gaink is runner-up and Raina hr.sec Chak Seri is 2nd runner-up 

The championship was a grand success, bringing together young martial artists who competed fiercely in various categories of the traditional Thang-Ta martial art. The event served as a platform for these talented athletes to demonstrate their dedication, discipline, and commitment to this ancient form of martial art, which holds significant cultural importance in the region.

The closing ceremony was graced by the esteemed presence of the Chief Guest, Sarpanch Sh. Raj Dev Singh Jamwal, who commended the participants for their outstanding performances and encouraged them to continue their hard work and dedication. He emphasized the importance of sports in building character and fostering a sense of discipline among the youth.

The Guest of Honour, Sh. Shakti Dutt Sharma, also addressed the gathering, appreciating the efforts of the organizers and the enthusiasm of the participants. He highlighted the role of such events in promoting traditional sports and preserving the rich cultural heritage of the region.

All the selected players from this championship will now represent District Jammu in the upcoming Union Territory (UT) level Thang-Ta Championship, furthering their journey in this esteemed martial art form. The organizers expressed their gratitude to all the participants, coaches, and supporters who made this event a grand success.
